Date: 05-08-2025


Aim
To accept birth year and current year as inputs.
To count leap years in the inclusive range.
To display the total number of leap years lived.
Algorithm
Read birthYear and currentYear (integers).
Initialize count = 0.
Loop year from birthYear to currentYear inclusive.
A year is leap if (year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0) or (year % 400 == 0).
If leap, increment count.
After loop, print count.
End program.
Program (Java)
import java.util.*;
class AgeCalculatorFunctions {
    private int birthYear, currentYear;
    public AgeCalculatorFunctions(int birthYear, int currentYear){
        this.birthYear = birthYear;
        this.currentYear = currentYear;
    }
    public int countLeapYears(){
        int count = 0;
        for (int y = birthYear; y <= currentYear; y++) {
            if ((y % 4 == 0 && y % 100 != 0) || (y % 400 == 0)) count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
public class LeapYearsLived {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int birth = Integer.parseInt(sc.nextLine().trim());
        int curr = Integer.parseInt(sc.nextLine().trim());
        AgeCalculatorFunctions a = new AgeCalculatorFunctions(birth, curr);
        System.out.println(a.countLeapYears());
        sc.close();
    }
}


Sample Output
Input: 1990 and 2023
Output: 8
Result
Counted leap years using the standard divisibility rules.
Displayed total leap years in the given inclusive range.
